You’re right to question that — the earlier steps included security pieces, but they weren’t stitched together as a proper security blueprint the way companies expect.

Let’s fix that and make it enterprise-grade security (end-to-end) 👇

🔐 🔥 COMPLETE SECURITY ARCHITECTURE (PROPERLY ADDED)

We’ll layer security at 5 levels:

🧱 1. EDGE SECURITY (Internet Protection)
✅ Application Gateway (WAF)

👉 This is your first security wall

Configure:
WAF Mode: Prevention (NOT Detection)
Rule Set: OWASP 3.2
Enable:
SQL Injection protection
XSS protection
File upload restrictions
✅ SSL Enforcement
Only allow:
HTTPS (443) ✅
HTTP (80) ❌ → Redirect to HTTPS
🌐 2. NETWORK SECURITY (MOST IMPORTANT)
✅ NSG (Network Security Groups)

Attach NSG to subnets:

🔹 app-subnet NSG
Rule	Action
Allow App Gateway subnet	✅
Deny Internet	❌
🔹 pe-subnet NSG
Rule	Action
Allow VNet	✅
Deny All Others	❌
🔹 vm-subnet NSG
Rule	Action
Allow Bastion	✅
Deny Internet RDP	❌
✅ Disable Public Access (CRITICAL)
Resource	Setting
App Service	Public Access ❌
SQL DB	Public Access ❌
✅ Private Endpoints
App Service → Private
SQL → Private

👉 No direct internet access

🔐 3. IDENTITY SECURITY (ZERO PASSWORD)
✅ Managed Identity

👉 App Service → SQL

✔ No credentials stored
✔ Secure authentication

✅ Azure AD (Entra ID)
Users synced from On-Prem AD
SQL access via AD users
✅ RBAC (Role-Based Access)

Example:

Role	Access
DevOps	Contributor
DBA	SQL Admin
App	DB Reader/Writer
🔑 4. SECRETS & CERTIFICATE SECURITY
✅ Key Vault

Store:

PFX certificate
Connection secrets (if any)
✅ Access Control
Only App Gateway can access cert
Use:
Access Policy / RBAC
🛡️ 5. DATA SECURITY
✅ Encryption at Rest
Azure SQL:
TDE (default enabled)
✅ Encryption in Transit
User → App Gateway → App → SQL

✔ All HTTPS
✔ TLS enforced

🚨 6. MONITORING + THREAT DETECTION
✅ Enable Logs
Application Gateway
Access logs
WAF logs
SQL
Auditing
Threat detection
✅ Azure Monitor + Alerts

Create alerts for:

CPU > 80%
Failed logins
High traffic spikes
💣 7. DDoS PROTECTION
Option:
Basic: Free
Standard: Recommended for production
